    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7889851>
    dc:description "FIGURES 23–29. Perlodinella kuenluensis (Šámal, 1935) comb. nov. from Tibet Plateau, Kunlun Mountains, China. Syntypus. Male: 23. Head and pronotum, dorsal. 24. Abdominal tip, with not everted paraprocts, caudal. 25. Terga 9–10 with chaetotaxy, paraproctal sclerite with hook, lateral. 26. Abdominal tip, lateral. 27. Collecting labels of the type specimen. 28. Meso-furcasternum, ventral. Photos were taken by P. Ciliberti. 29. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912, from Yangtze River Basin, China, deposited in ZIN with the “Cotype” label. Male, the paraproctal sclerite with hook." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7889851/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7889853>
    dc:description "FIGURES 30–34. Perlodinella kuenluensis (Šámal, 1935) comb. nov. from Tibet Plateau, Kunlun Mountains, China. Syntypus. Female: 30. Head and pronotum, dorsal. 31. Abdominal tip, with subgenital plate, ventral. 32. Abdomen with subgenital plate and eggs, ventral. 33. Eggs. 34. Collecting labels of the type specimen. Photos were taken by P. Ciliberti." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7889853/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

